    streamFind for mass spectrometry with R

ProcessingSettings S3 class constructor, methods and functions

Source: R/class_S3_ProcessingSettings.R
ProcessingSettings.Rd

Creates a ProcessingSettings S3 class object. The ProcessingSettings are used in streamFind for processing data in a given data class method.

Usage

ProcessingSettings(
  call = NA_character_,
  algorithm = NA_character_,
  parameters = NULL,
  software = NA_character_,
  developer = NA_character_,
  contact = NA_character_,
  link = NA_character_,
  doi = NA_character_
)

# S3 method for ProcessingSettings
validate(x = NULL)

# S3 method for ProcessingSettings
asJSON(x)

# S3 method for ProcessingSettings
export(x, format = "json", name = "settings", path = getwd())

as.ProcessingSettings(value)

Arguments

call

Character of length one with the name of the method where the processing settings are to be applied.

algorithm

Character of length one with the name of the algorithm to be used.

parameters

List with parameters specific for the method call and algorithm.

software

Character of length one with the name of the software or package.

developer

Character of length one with the name of the developer/s.

contact

Character of length one with the email of the developer.

link

Character of length one with the documentation web link.

doi

Character of length one with the DOI of algorithm.

x

A ProcessingSettings S3 class object.

format

X.

name

X.

path

X.

value

A list to be checked and/or converted to ProcessingSettings S3 class.

Value

A ProcessingSettings S3 class

Details

See the documentation of the method where the processing settings are to be applied for more information about applicable algorithms and parameters.

Methods (by generic)

  • validate(ProcessingSettings): Validates a ProcessingSettings S3 class object, returning a logical value of length one.

  • asJSON(ProcessingSettings): Converts a ProcessingSettings S3 class object to a JSON string.

  • export(ProcessingSettings): Exports a ProcessingSettings S3 class object to a JSON or RDS file.

Functions

  • as.ProcessingSettings(): Converts the argument in a ProcessingSettings S3 class object.
